verbs.description: outbook (third-person singular simple present outbooks, present participle outbooking, simple past and past participle outbooked)

examples: Supervising the front desk, she regularly outbooked her peers by £1,000 a night.

entries.meaning: (transitive, chess) To surpass in one's knowledge of book moves.
examples: Then on move 13, Deep Thought II surprisingly found itself outbooked and in a difficult position.
